        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 2:50PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 249 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles west of Pringle, or 20 miles east of Dumas, moving northeast at
10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Stinnett, Morse, and Pringle.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
